00:14:23.260 --> 00:14:25.260
is the leading cause of death worldwide.

00:14:25.260 --> 00:14:27.260
1.1 million Americans

00:14:27.260 --> 00:14:30.260
suffer heart attacks yearly.

00:14:30.260 --> 00:14:32.260
4.8 million

00:14:32.260 --> 00:14:34.260
suffer cardiac failure.

00:14:34.260 --> 00:14:36.260
Stem cells may be used

00:14:36.260 --> 00:14:38.260
to deliver growth factors

00:14:38.260 --> 00:14:40.260
to repair damaged heart muscle

00:14:40.260 --> 00:14:42.260
or be differentiated

00:14:42.260 --> 00:14:44.260
into heart muscle cells

00:14:44.260 --> 00:14:46.260
to restore heart function.

00:14:46.260 --> 00:14:49.260
There are 170 clinical trials

00:14:49.260 --> 00:14:53.260
investigating the role of stem cells in heart disease.

00:14:53.260 --> 00:14:56.260
While still in a research phase,

00:14:56.260 --> 00:14:59.260
stem cells may one day herald

00:14:59.260 --> 00:15:02.260
a quantum leap in the field of cardiology.

00:15:03.260 --> 00:15:06.260
Stem cells provide hope for new beginnings --

00:15:06.260 --> 00:15:09.260
small, incremental steps,

00:15:09.260 --> 00:15:12.260
cells rather than organs,

00:15:12.260 --> 00:15:15.260
repair rather than replacement.

00:15:15.260 --> 00:15:18.260
Stem cell therapies

00:15:18.260 --> 00:15:22.260
may one day reduce the need for donor organs.

00:15:22.260 --> 00:15:24.260
Powerful new technologies

00:15:24.260 --> 00:15:26.260
always present enigmas.

00:15:26.260 --> 00:15:28.260
As we speak,

00:15:28.260 --> 00:15:31.260
the world's first human embryonic stem cell trial for spinal cord injury

00:15:31.260 --> 00:15:33.260
is currently underway

00:15:33.260 --> 00:15:36.260
following the USFDA approval.

00:15:36.260 --> 00:15:38.260
And in the U.K.,

00:15:38.260 --> 00:15:40.260
neural stem cells to treat stroke

00:15:40.260 --> 00:15:43.260
are being investigated in a phase one trial.

00:15:44.260 --> 00:15:47.260
The research success that we celebrate today

00:15:47.260 --> 00:15:49.260
has been made possible

00:15:49.260 --> 00:15:53.260
by the curiosity and contribution and commitment

00:15:53.260 --> 00:15:55.260
of individual scientists

00:15:55.260 --> 00:15:57.260
and medical pioneers.

00:15:57.260 --> 00:16:00.260
Each one has his story.

00:16:00.260 --> 00:16:03.260
My story has been about my journey

00:16:03.260 --> 00:16:05.260
from organs to cells --

00:16:05.260 --> 00:16:07.260
a journey through controversy,

00:16:07.260 --> 00:16:09.260
inspired by hope --

00:16:09.260 --> 00:16:12.260
hope that, as we age,

00:16:12.260 --> 00:16:15.260
you and I may one day celebrate longevity

00:16:15.260 --> 00:16:17.260
with an improved quality of life.

00:16:17.260 --> 00:16:19.260
Thank you.

